# Copy to .scrub-secrets.local (gitignored, NEVER committed), then fill with YOUR
# private words — anything that must never reach a public commit:
#   OS username, real name(s), private email handles, machine hostname, private
#   nicknames / relationship terms, home coordinates.
# One extended-regex pattern per line. Lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# The scanner reads .scrub-secrets.local and fails if any pattern is found in tracked
# content or commit messages. Only THIS .example ships; it holds no real words.
#
# Do NOT list public code identifiers you legitimately ship (they would false-positive) —
# put those paths in scripts/scrub-allow.txt instead.
#
# examples (replace with your own):
# myusername
# Firstname Lastname
# my-laptop-hostname
# private-nickname
